ActionBar

public static final int[] ActionBar
============================================ Attributes used to style the Action Bar. These should be set on your theme; the default actionBarStyle will propagate them to the correct elements as needed. Please Note: when overriding attributes for an ActionBar style you must specify each attribute twice: once with the "android:" namespace prefix and once without.

Includes the following attributes:

AttributeDescription
edu.oit.cst407.project:background Specifies a background drawable for the action bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:backgroundSplit Specifies a background drawable for the bottom component of a split action bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:backgroundStacked Specifies a background drawable for a second stacked row of the action bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:customNavigationLayout Specifies a layout for custom navigation.
edu.oit.cst407.project:displayOptions Options affecting how the action bar is displayed.
edu.oit.cst407.project:divider Specifies the drawable used for item dividers.
edu.oit.cst407.project:height Specifies a fixed height.
edu.oit.cst407.project:homeLayout Specifies a layout to use for the "home" section of the action bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:icon Specifies the drawable used for the application icon.
edu.oit.cst407.project:indeterminateProgressStyle Specifies a style resource to use for an indeterminate progress spinner.
edu.oit.cst407.project:itemPadding Specifies padding that should be applied to the left and right sides of system-provided items in the bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:logo Specifies the drawable used for the application logo.
edu.oit.cst407.project:navigationMode The type of navigation to use.
edu.oit.cst407.project:progressBarPadding Specifies the horizontal padding on either end for an embedded progress bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:progressBarStyle Specifies a style resource to use for an embedded progress bar.
edu.oit.cst407.project:subtitle Specifies subtitle text used for navigationMode="normal"
edu.oit.cst407.project:subtitleTextStyle Specifies a style to use for subtitle text.
edu.oit.cst407.project:title Specifies title text used for navigationMode="normal"
edu.oit.cst407.project:titleTextStyle Specifies a style to use for title text.

See Also:
